issue.title: [Feature Request: c#] Provide Onnxruntime related Nugets consisting of contributed Operators as shared library

labels.name: feature request
labels.description: request for unsupported feature or enhancement

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
### Describe the feature request

- We now have improved [documentation ](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/12896)on how to consume (through registration) custom operators which is relevant to c# users
- There is a new effort in [refactoring the c and c++ API](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/12998) for dealing with custom operators, which I hope will be relevant to this feature request.

It is time we consider how to provide different Onnxruntime related NuGets which consist of shared libraries that expose [contributed operators](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/main/docs/ContribOperators.md) similar in format to [custom_op_library.dll](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/2f9b358d16885c8330eaa34a932315e3b176082c/csharp/test/Microsoft.ML.OnnxRuntime.Tests.NetCoreApp/InferenceTest.netcore.cs#L634) and therefore accessible to c# users


### Describe scenario use cases

[Reference](https://github.com/dotnet/TorchSharp/discussions/526)

#### use case 1
- [ ] Evaluate the feasibility to use TorchSharp to integrate custom operators and export to ONNX.
- [ ] Use ML.NET to register the integrated custom operators used in the exported ONNX model before consuming the ONNX model

#### use case 2
- [ ] Instead of integrating custom operators as stated in use case 1, integrate existing contributed operators distributed by ONNXRUNTIME
- [ ] Use ML.NET to register the integrated contributed operators used in the exported ONNX model before consuming the ONNX model

body:
This proposed categorization will facilitate discussion and issue project management of existing feature requests/discussions:

- [ ] [[Documentation]: Overview of C# Workflow for consuming "Augmented" Onnx model with Custom Operators](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/11564)
- [ ] [C# pre and postprocessing with opencvsharp for onnxruntime](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/discussions/11411)
- [X] [OpenCV Image Decoder & SuperResolution CustomOps](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime-extensions/pull/295)

Our operator need to be backward compatible so it is not feasible to change domain without breaking existing application.

I think adding some tags in operator documentation might serve the purpose.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    image-->|com.microsoft.vision\nops| onnx\nmodel-->|com.microsoft.vision\nops| output\nimage
```

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    text-->|com.microsoft.nlp\nops| onnx\nmodel-->|com.microsoft.nlp\nops| output\ntext
```

issue.title: [Performance] how I can stop or truncate the generation in onnx gpt-2 model with the beam search option

labels.name: model:transformer

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
### Describe the issue

I want to stop the generation of gpt2 in order to reduce the time to get the answers, how I can stop or truncate the generation in onnx gpt-2 model with the beam search option?

I run gpt2 in C++ (with CPU) and the answers take on average a time of 8 seconds.

For example:
input: "It was a new experience for me"

output: "_It was a new experience for me, and I couldn't wait to get my hands on it. The first thing you need to do is download the zip file from here: http://www.amazon.com/gp/trade_" 

For the application that I am doing is enoug with the anwser until the dot: "_It was a new experience for me, and I couldn't wait to get my hands on it_." In this way, the calculation after the dot is a inncesary expense.

I have tried to force the value of eos_token_id in the convert_generatoin.py, but it dosen't work.

```
#eos_token_id = config.eos_token_id
eos_token_id = 13 #TODO(Jorge): 13 is the dot in my gpt vocabulary
    pad_token_id = config.eos_token_id if is_gpt2 else config.pad_token_id
    vocab_size = config.vocab_size
```

I appreciate any suggestions, thanks!

### To reproduce

I have exported the GPT 2 model with the Beam Search option with the following command:
`python convert_generation.py -m gpt2 --output C:\\workspace\\onnxruntime\\onnxruntime\\python\\tools\\transformers\\Output2\\gpt2_beam_search.onnx`

### Urgency

I want to publish a demo video game in november 2022.

Windows

Windows 10 64 bits

Released Package

Default CPU

### Model File

GPT2

No

issue.title: [Feature Request] C# : how I can innovate the language generation using com.microsoft.nlp contributed ops?

labels.name: feature request
labels.description: request for unsupported feature or enhancement

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
#### Original title
C# : how I can innovate the language generation in onnx gpt-2 model with the beam search and/or other custom operators of similar class (Deep NLP)

### Describe the feature request

[how I can stop or truncate the generation in onnx gpt-2 model with the beam search option](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/13088) provides an **unmet** Deep NLP use case, especially langauge generation.

Currently, early stopping needs to be enabled with appropriately generated eos token to customize BeamSearch results



### Describe scenario use case

The [feedback ](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/13088#issuecomment-1264791404)from user suggests additional ways to customize BeamSearch is needed to provide more optimum language generation results.

This is just with BeamSearch, how about other Contributed Operators of similar class? e.g. GreedySearch discussed in [Classify Contributed Ops ](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/13084)

##### nlp
com.microsoft.nlp
- [com.microsoft.nlp.BeamSearch](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/main/docs/ContribOperators.md#com.microsoft.BeamSearch)
- [com.microsoft.nlp.GreedySearch](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/main/docs/ContribOperators.md#com.microsoft.GreedySearch)

issue.body:
Is there any plan to add classes of torchvision/ops?

roi_align and boxes are required, they are not implemented in TorchSharp
```
return torch.ops.torchvision.roi_align(
        input, rois, spatial_scale, output_size[0], output_size[1], sampling_ratio, aligned
    )
```
